sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45902
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is designed to detect the presence of botulism toxin type C. It is composed of a ribosome binding site, a fluorescent protein (SBFP2), a cleavage site that the toxin attacks (Syntaxin-1A), and a 10x his-tag. Ideally, this should be able to be purified after production using a nickel or copper column, eluted, and then mixed with the sample. If the toxin is in solution, it will cleave the Syntaxin-1A sequence, separating the fluorescent protein from the his-tag. This means that if the solution is run through a column again, the fluorescent protein should come out during the flow throughs rather than the elutions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chad Lawrence Nielsen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Composite part created from existing parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Syntaxin-1A is from humans, eukaryotic organisms, so it may not work with E. coli. A blue fluorescent protein was chosen because this part is part of a set for a class project and will be different from GFP and RFP that will be released by different strains of botulism toxin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SBFP2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for orange fluorescent protein (OFP). Fluorescent proteins are useful tools for visualizing and quantifying protein expression in cells. OFP is yet another fluorescent protein, like GFP, that can be utilized as a reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: George McArthur IV
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: OFP was cloned from the tentacles of ''Cerianthus'' sp., a tube anemone. The original sequence was obtained from GenBank (VERSION AY296063.1, GI:31616578).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was codon-optimized for expression in ''E. coli''. The following restriction enzyme sites were also removed: EcoRI, NotI, XbaI, SpeI, PstI, NheI, AvrII, ApoI, MfeI, NsiI, SbfI.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45901
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chad Lawrence Nielsen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Back translation of the amino acid sequence for human Syntaxin-1A optimized for E. coli. Should be able to be cleaved by BoNT/C.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 10x-Histidine tag with double stop codon TAATAA to allow for better extraction of tagged products and protein termination in a single part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Miller
